% ReadTT  (MEX FILE) Reads an NSMA TT file%% [t, wv] = ReadTT(fn, records_to_get, record_units)%% INPUTS:%    fn = file name string%    records_to_get (optional) = an array that is either a range of values (start and end) or a list%    record_units (optional) =  1: timestamp list%                               2: record number list%					            3: range of timestamps%					            4: range of records%	 (if only fn is passed in then the entire file is opened)% OUTPUTS:%    t = n x 1: timestamps of each spike in file%    wv = n x 4 x 32 waveforms%% Reads both sun TTfiles and NT-TTfiles and distinguishes them by checking if a header %   exists (for sun TTfiles) or not (for NT-TTfiles).% Checks for standard Neuralynx header if present (in Cheeath versions >= 1.3) and %   automatically skips header.%% PL 9/00, version 5.1, last modified 4/14/01 by SC% cowen 4/14/01: Modified to allow partial loading.